Thank you for taking the time to meet today.

Today we:
Looked into the host list that was being used by the ADI scan as it appears ADI hasn't scanned successfully in some time.

The list is being generated by a custom script and was failing to update. We then created a new version of the job and ran it to see if it would populate the table as expected.
Our next steps are:

You will:
Monitor the ADI scan job to verify it runs succesfully.
If it does, check the AIC logs to verify that the errors have stopped.

Thank you for taking the time to meet today.

Today we:
Set the ExpirationState to 2 in the SA_AIC_ResourceAccessRequests table for each of the affected SIDs in the logs.
Monitored the logs for 5 minutes to ensure the issue did not return.

Our next steps are:
You will:
Check the logs in the morning to ensure that the events have not reoccurred

I will:
Keep the ticket open until tomorrow morning to verify the issue is resolved.



Thank you,

Subject: RE: RE:Netwrix Support Ticket #425583 -  - Unable to find domain for member errors for expiring access to shares    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0HgOoy:ref ]

TextBody:
Hello Connie,

Thank you for your time and patience on this issue and I am glad that we were able to get your issue resolved for you. 
The following is a summary of the ticket for your records.

Issue:
Logs are rotating quickly due to AIC trying to remove permissions from users that it cannot find a domain for.

2024-10-30 10:14:54 -- Error -- Exception:
2024-10-30 10:14:54 -- Error -- Message: Unable to find domain for member: S-1-5-21-3542245194-2364831464-1968421150-114106
2024-10-30 10:14:54 -- Error -- Type: System.InvalidOperationException
2024-10-30 10:14:54 -- Error -- StackTrace:
at AccessInformationCenter.Model.Membership.ActiveDirectoryMembership.Execute(StorageDataContext dc, String domainName, MembershipRequest request)
at AccessInformationCenter.Model.Membership.MembershipAction.Execute(StorageDataContext dc, String feature, String invokerName, String invokerSid, IEnumerable`1 changes, Nullable`1 changeId)


Cause:
The issue is caused when a user is granted temporary permissions to a resources, but the user is deleted prior to the permission expiring. When the permission expires the AIC console keeps trying to remove the user but cannot find the information for it.

Resolution:
Set the ExpirationState to 2 in the SA_AIC_ResourceAccessRequests table for each SID encountering the problem. This will set the permission state to complete.

At this time I will be closing your ticket out for you. This case can be re-opened at any time if any related issues return. 
Please feel free to reach out to the Netwrix team if you have any additional questions or would like assistance with any issues. Following this email, you will receive an automated confirmation that the case has been closed.
You will also receive a survey link, it would help us greatly to improve our support service if you could provide any feedback that you may have regarding your experience with this case.

Thank you,
Ian Ranstrom
Senior Technical Support Engineer
